cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on improving the training procedures and architectural features of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for two applications: semi-supervised learning and generating visually realistic images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since GANs are a type of neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses architectural features, cs.GR (Graphics) could also be a possible sub-category.
